      <guid>https://blog.indonesiadot.com/2019/09/02/all-about-kubernetes/</guid>
      <description>Kubernetes Container runtime with docker # Install Docker CE ## Set up the repository ### Install required packages. yum install yum-utils device-mapper-persistent-data lvm2 ### Add Docker repository. yum-config-manager \ --add-repo \ https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo ## Install Docker CE. yum update &amp;amp;&amp;amp; yum install docker-ce-18.06.2.ce ## Create /etc/docker directory. mkdir /etc/docker # Setup daemon. cat &amp;gt; /etc/docker/daemon.json &amp;lt;&amp;lt;EOF { &amp;#34;exec-opts&amp;#34;: [&amp;#34;native.cgroupdriver=systemd&amp;#34;], &amp;#34;log-driver&amp;#34;: &amp;#34;json-file&amp;#34;, &amp;#34;log-opts&amp;#34;: { &amp;#34;max-size&amp;#34;: &amp;#34;100m&amp;#34; }, &amp;#34;storage-driver&amp;#34;: &amp;#34;overlay2&amp;#34;, &amp;#34;storage-opts&amp;#34;: [ &amp;#34;overlay2.override_kernel_check=true&amp;#34; ] } EOF mkdir -p /etc/systemd/system/docker.</description>
